### Bug description:

I have validation error in valid date. The date is formatted ISO 8601. For example, "2016-12-03T15:00:00.000Z".

The date is converted to Date object in directive, as below:

```
ctrl.$formatters.push(function(modelValue){
  return modelValue === null ? null : new Date(modelValue);
});
```

At the time, `parseDateString` function in datepickerPopup/popup.js is failed. `viewValue` parameter receive `modelValue`. 

```
function parseDateString(viewValue) {
    var date = dateParser.parse(viewValue, dateFormat, $scope.date);
    ...
}
```

```
function validator(modelValue, viewValue) {
    var value = modelValue || viewValue;

    ...

    if (angular.isString(value)) {
      return !isNaN(parseDateString(value));
    }

    return false;
}
```

For example, `modelValue = '2016-12-03T15:00:00.000Z'`, `viewValue = '2016-12-04'` and `uib-datepicker-popup="yyyy-MM-dd"`.

### Link to minimally-working plunker that reproduces the issue:

http://plnkr.co/edit/sMNKxk

### Version of Angular, UIBS, and Bootstrap

Angular: 1.5.9

UIBS: 2.3.0

Bootstrap: 3.3.7

As someone who frequents the angular-ui bootstrap documentation website, and has to look at some of the older docs (thank you for keeping those around!), please note that it is difficult to select older items from the "previous docs" menu.

Perhaps add custom css as follows so the menu list can be usable again.

```
.navbar-nav>li>.dropdown-menu {
    ....
    overflow-y: auto;
    max-height: 400px;
}
```

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2031435/20533509/5a03aea8-b0a3-11e6-8390-9ee3bc1a9b19.png)

In my application i have a lots of popups so i cannot attach particular event on every modal open or closed state so that's why i need ability to trigger event on closed and on opened state when any modal opens or closed.

Example: 

``` javascript

$uibModalStack.opened.then(function(){
// Trigger when any modal is opened
})

$uibModalStack.closed.then(function(){
// Trigger when any modal is closed
})
```
